//ldd:source lowerer.ly
//ldd:why "AST → LIR translation. Flattens expressions into SSA-like temp definitions, resolves type sugar, handles error results. Two-phase architecture matching Go implementation."

// ## Architecture
//
// The lowerer converts a type-checked AST into an LProgram:
//
// 1. register_block: Collect all struct/class/enum/interface/function
// declarations into Dict registries. Populates variant tags, class
// fields, enum variants.
// 2. lower_file: Walk all blocks, lower each declaration to LIR.
// Functions lowered by walking body statements, flattening expressions
// into temp chains.
//
// Key transforms:
// - Enums → LTyTaggedUnion, match → switch on variant tag
// - Classes → LTyClassHandle (heap pointer), field access via class_get/set
// - Try (?) → extract error → null check → early return → extract value
// - Generators → goroutine + channel pattern
// - Lambdas → LExprFuncLit with params and body
// - String interpolation → LExprFormat with parts list
// - Impl blocks → forwarding wrapper methods

// ## Invariants — Two-Phase Architecture
//
// The lowerer uses two phases, matching the Go implementation:
// 1. register_block: collect all struct/class/enum/interface/function
// declarations into Dict registries (no code generation)
// 2. lower_file: walk all blocks, lower declarations to LIR
//
// This ensures forward references resolve correctly. Phase 1 must run
// across ALL blocks before Phase 2 begins (same pattern as checker).

// ## Invariants — Type Lowering Fallback
//
// lower_type() resolves AST TypeExpr to LType. For identifier types, it
// checks: primitives → structs → classes → enums → type aliases.
// If nothing matches, it assumes LTyTypeVar (generic type parameter).
//
// Typos in type names silently become type variables — the checker should
// catch these but has gaps during bootstrap.

// ## Invariants — Enum Variant Disambiguation
//
// Multiple enums may share variant names (e.g., Ident exists in ExprKind,
// PatternKind, TypeExprKind). The lowerer must consult the checker's type
// annotation on each expression to determine which enum a variant belongs
// to. Without this, last-writer-wins in the variant lookup map causes
// wrong enum variant construction.
//
// Three levels of disambiguation:
// 1. lower_call/lower_ident: check resolved_type to pick correct enum
// 2. Match lowering: use enum-specific variant maps (keyed by enum name)
// 3. Variant constructor: inherit field types from enum declaration

// ## Invariants — Error Type Resolution
//
// The Lyric `error` interface maps to LTyErrorResult for (T, error) tuples.
// In the Go compiler, the checker types `error` as TyInterface; the lowerer
// must detect TyInterface with name "error" and map to LTyErrorResult.
//
// ErrorResult fields: ._0 → .value (the T), ._1 → .error (const char*).
// Return of (T, error) tuples wraps with lyric_ok/lyric_err in C.

// ## Invariants — Expression Flattening
//
// Every lowerExpr call emits LStmtTempDef statements and returns an LValue.
// The temp counter (next_temp) is per-function, reset at lower_func start.
// Backends never see nested expressions.

// ## Invariants — Class Field Defaults
//
// Class fields can have default values. The lowerer stores these during
// registration. During struct literal lowering for class allocations,
// any field not explicitly provided is filled with its default value.

// ## Invariants — Short-Circuit Lowering
//
// Logical && and || are NOT lowered as binary ops (would cause eager
// evaluation). Instead they're lowered to if-statements:
// - `a && b` → `let mut t = a; if t { t = b }`
// - `a || b` → `let mut t = a; if !t { t = b }`
// This prevents segfaults from null access on short-circuit paths.

// ## Invariants — Statement Buffer Management
//
// The lowerer uses save_stmts()/restore_stmts() to temporarily redirect
// emitted statements to a sub-buffer (e.g. for if-else bodies, while
// conditions, match arms). The previous buffer is restored after the
// nested processing completes. This is analogous to the checker's
// push_scope()/pop_scope() pattern.


// lowerer.ly:13
class Lowerer {
  class_defaults: Dict<Sym, Expr>?
  class_fields: Dict<Sym, Dict<Sym, LType>>?
  classes: Dict<Sym, ClassDecl>?
  current_func_return: LType?
  enum_variant_fields: Dict<Sym, [TupleField]>?
  enum_variant_tags: Dict<Sym, i32>?
  enums: Dict<Sym, EnumDecl>?
  func_sigs: Dict<Sym, FuncDecl>?
  impl_method_renames: Dict<Sym, string>?
  import_aliases: Dict<Sym, string>?
  interfaces: Dict<Sym, InterfaceDecl>?
  lowered_ifaces: Dict<Sym, LInterfaceDecl>?
  scope: Dict<Sym, LType>?
  stmts: [LStmt?]
  structs: Dict<Sym, StructDecl>?
  temp_id: i32
  type_aliases: Dict<Sym, TypeExpr>?
  unit_variants: Dict<Sym, bool>?
  variant_to_enum: Dict<Sym, string>?
}
